        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3: Monoschelobates parvus Balogh and Mahunka, 1969: A – body dorsally; B – body ventrally (gnathosoma and legs not illustrated); C – prodorsum and anterior part of notogaster laterally (gnathosoma and legs not illustrated); D – lamellar seta; E – sensillus; F – pedotectum II, discidium and epimeral setae 3c, 4c in dissected specimen; G – left genital plate and epimaral setae 3a, 4b; H – left anal plate and adanal setae ad1-ad3; I – claw on leg I. Scale bars (A-C) 50 µm, scale bar (D-F, I) 10 µm, scale bar (G, H) 10 µm." ;
